Heat the oil in a 1-gallon pot over medium heat, then add the onion, carrot, and celery and cook for about 5 minutes. Add any of the other suggested vegetables and continue cooking gently for another 5 minutes. Add the bay leaf, herbs, and salt, then cover with about 6 cups of cold water. Bring to a boil, then lower the heat and simmer for 20-30 minutes. Turn off the heat and let it steep for a few more minutes. Strain and cool. It will keep, refrigerated, up to 3 days, or frozen for up to 2 months.